##The diary of a psychologist (week 1)

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

On February 9, Tang Wei, director of the Department of Mental Psychology of Wenzhou Kangning Hospital Group, arrived in Wuhan with the Third Group of Zhejiang medical team from Hubei Province to participate in the psychological crisis intervention in the front line of Wuhan's fight against the epidemic and provide psychological assistance to medical staff and patients.

During the period, director Tang Wei in the diary to record the medical staff to overcome difficulties, fighting against the epidemic front-line experience. At eight o'clock, after obtaining the consent of the author, the extracts are compiled and published in stages.

The wife says to Wuhan Direction: I lend my husband to you

Sunday, February 9, Sunny Hangzhou

Early in the morning, I was answering the hotline, was interrupted by a hurried phone call, a look is Chairman Guan Weili, this time he called me must have something important, this is not the first time.

"Tang Wei, get your things ready and go to Hangzhou tomorrow morning at nine o'clock. Join up with the provincial medical team and go to Wuhan. Will you? " The chairman's voice was firm. We'd been together for 20 years, and he knew my temper and my character, and he knew I didn't have to think about it, and he knew I didn't have to think about it, and he called me in the middle of the night and left in the morning after the 2008 earthquake in Wenchuan County.

After twenty + years of crisis intervention, I had a hunch that this time it would be on the ground. I didn't expect the country to act so soon.

Pack your things, get your supplies, and think more about how you're going to do your job. This time is different, the main way of epidemic prevention is isolation, but we psychological assistance, psychotherapy best face-to-face, how to do face-to-face themselves and not infected, this is a problem. Protection, in particular, is a new concept for US psychotherapists. What should I do if a mentally ill person becomes ill and attacks impulsively? What about my hazmat suit, or one of the other crew's Hazmat suits? These are unprecedented questions.

I was so sleepy that I heard my wife call me: You should get up and go.

After years of crisis intervention, my wife, accustomed to my sudden departure from home, quietly helped me pack my bags. This time she was clearly seen with tears in her eyes, pointing in the direction of Wuhan: I lent my husband to you, you must give him back to me.

Out of the daughter ran to ask me, Father Wuhan so dangerous you go to do? Looking at my daughter's innocent face, I said: Wuhan has a lot of monsters, dad to fight monsters, fight monsters will come back. The daughter knows, fight monster is hero, hero will come back.

Arrived at the hospital at 8:00, did not let his wife, afraid of sad, she did not come. All the hospital leaders are waiting for me. After arranging the work of the department, the hospital organized a brief ceremony. The director of the Wenzhou Health Commission and the President of the Board of Directors of the hospital gave me high hopes and asked me to come back safely.

Arrived in Hangzhou and met with director Liu Zhihong, deputy director of Hangzhou Yining Hospital and Director of the Mental Health Center. After a short training, after attending the oath-taking meeting held by the provincial government leaders, dozens of buses carrying us, carrying the aid of the people of Zhejiang to the airport.

At 4:40, three charter planes shot into the sky.

Wuhan, here we come.

Wuhan Wins Hubei Wins Hubei Wins Hubei wins the whole country wins!

"In Times of national crisis, we must shoulder our responsibilities. "

Monday, February 10th, in the shade of Wuhan

I went to bed at 1:30 last night and was awakened by the noise in the morning. Then I ran to the hall. There were many team members here and there. They were all excited and solemn.

A few little bald nurses were particularly noticeable. It was part of the job, and I was too embarrassed to take a picture, so I kept it in my head.

People are always in a hurry, don't have time to call it out, can't see who's who, everyone just shows two eyes.

Director Liu Zhihong and I desperately want to get the task, but even such a simple wish is difficult to achieve, now material security more than psychological security, it seems that we have to keep looking for work.

In the afternoon, Director Wang Heqiu and his colleagues from Litongde Hospital in Zhejiang Province went to another place, leaving me and director Liu alone and lonely to wait.

Received a lot of greetings in the evening, suffering to see the truth, thank you in the heart of the old Tang in.

In the dead of night, eighty old mother called, originally thought that mother can not bear, go without telling her, feel guilty to her mother. But she told me, you are a doctor, this time has to assume responsibility, the country is in trouble, must assume everyone's responsibility... mother's words to strengthen my determination here.

Sleep with nothing to lose.

"Rest assured, logistics are not an issue. "

Tuesday, Feb. 11, light rain turns to overcast in Wuhan

After yesterday's rush-hour, today up the spirit obviously improved, have not yet recovered from the shock to receive the order to transfer. No one knows where we are, no one knows who to ask, and no one seems to know, and no one who knows knows knows where we are.

The weather was cold, everyone was in a heavy mood, all the way did not joke, are looking at mobile phone information, to call family and friends, report safe, noon we rushed to Mulan Grassland Resort, only to know that we are here to take over a shelter hospital.

Logistical problems, we did not eat and drink, there is nothing here, there is no quilt, bedding, there is no hot water, some members of the team appeared restless mood. As team members of the crisis intervention team, we came out to calm everyone down, let everyone go back to the room, slowly resolved. At 10:00 p.m. , the quilts and quilts arrive, but it's mostly for the summer. It was the only way the team could cope with the cold weather.

We were told this afternoon to get into the shelter hospital, but we had to deal with protective gear like the suits. It was difficult for us, because we had been told to leave in less than eight hours, and there was no time to prepare at night, and since we were a psychiatric hospital, we didn't usually have these things, and just when we didn't know what to do, guan Weili Chairman of the board and Wang Hongyue general manager of the call, told all problems will be resolved, rest assured that the work, logistics is not a problem. At 9:00 in the evening, Ye Aiqun teacher called, tell how to do a good job of protection and disinfection, good intentions, book to Time Square hate less, usually ye teacher stressed the hand-washing disinfection finally have a useful place.

In bed at night, answering the hotline. Now I have to overcome the cold weather, can not open air conditioning, no hot water, only the wife's words of care, only to make me feel warm, support I have the ability to continue to complete the mission.

Two guys in their 50s, arguing their faces off

Wednesday, February 12, cloudy to sunny in Wuhan

After a cold night, I woke up in the morning and found that there was fog in my breath. It seemed that Wuhan was not cold in general. Early in the morning and director Liu Zhihong together to find organization, mission, but with the integrated team team, we are basically marginalized, it seems that no one pays attention to us, a sense of loss, we have to work as soon as possible.

On the way, I met a nurse Xiao Liu of the provincial people's Hospital who came down from the shelter hospital, she told us about the reaction of the people who had come earlier: "When we entered the shelter hospital, the local nurses couldn't help crying when they saw us. They said we couldn't bear it if you didn't come again. There are so many patients, I don't know when I'm going to finish it, it's like I'll never finish it..."

Xiao Liu's nurses work in four shifts. Each nurse has to manage 100-150 patients, making rounds twice a day, mainly to see if the patients'conditions have changed, whether they need to be transferred to another hospital, and whether they need to make necessary examinations. They have no rest after work, and they work four shifts in a row, because there's no one left to cover for them.

According to our interviews, there's a lot of pressure on the people in the shelter. One is the shelter hospital does not have so many rescue equipment, and another is too many personnel, this scene, whether to quarantine the crowd or staff are psychological crushing.

Wuhan, it takes courage, isolation ward too test physical and psychological stress. In the Resident Hotel, some rooms at night will be out of the sound of crying, and even roar. At present, everyone in a room, according to the requirements of the hospital, we can not close contact, also can not go to the room, in fact, everyone knows what is going on, but the next day will pretend nothing, continue to work. The stress on the medical staff was extreme. I suppose this is what the provincial office sent us for.

Nurse Liu talked with us for half an hour or so and said it was much better to talk with you. Director Liu and I also gave her some psychological protection advice, empathy, listening, venting, and some relaxation techniques. This must be the first case of face-to-face psychological assistance in an infected area.

Director Liu Zhihong and I are under a lot of pressure. Noon to eat, director Liu drafted a work plan, issued the assistance team members wechat group.

After dinner, I was told that some people would go into the shelter hospital tomorrow. Everyone should learn to wear protective clothing. In order to save supplies, everyone should use diapers, because diapers are not in short supply and can be bought.

For me and director Liu, wearing clothes is really a problem, I two repeated practice, seriously experience, more serious than the exam.

There's been a disagreement about who's going down to the shelter hospital. Considering Director Liu is old and not in good health, I decided to enter the shelter hospital, but director Liu insisted that it was a matter of two people, we are representing Zhejiang Province, representing Wenzhou, representing Corning Hospital, how can we be deserters? Besides, he's a party member. How can he not get in when the chips are down? For the first time, two of us in our 50s had a heated argument, and we both knew what it meant to go in. Finally decided not to come down, then call the chairman of the board. It was 3-1. I got in three times, he got in one. Director Liu was very unhappy to accept the task, but he proposed that every day I enter the shelter he went with me, waiting for me outside, together back. And suddenly I burst into tears.

"I shall return in triumph. "

Thursday, Feb. 13, in Wuhan on a Cloudy Day

Now every day to do is in the micro-network access consultation, and we aid Wuhan Medical Team in Zhejiang docking. The medical team leader has informed all the members of our working methods and locations, finally have a sense of belonging.

News Release Today Wuhan added 13,436 new cases, since this morning I have received dozens of calls, hundreds of Wechat, are greetings, looking forward to my triumphant return. Thank these people who care about me, I came to help Wuhan, I will return home in triumph.

The afternoon suddenly came to inform, let Zhejiang a part of the team members support Wuhan four hospitals, where is the serious disease area. We Zhejiang team these days like commandos, where the epidemic was heavy was transferred to where, director Liu Zhihong and I went downstairs to help them carry luggage and supplies, a team member hug separation, several girls can no longer restrain, tears covered their faces.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
She said she was falling apart

Friday, February 14, light to moderate rain in Wuhan

Cold and wet weather makes us a bit difficult to adapt to, in order to ventilate the room to open the doors and windows to keep the air flowing, but open the door room will be full of the smell of disinfectant, let a person feel dizzy.

At present, there is no problem with living security, three packed meals a day, there will be a piece of fruit, which should be very good in the current situation, starting today, I don't know why, there is always a power cut, and I heard from other team members that the weather is cold, and the power can't keep up with them, so much for logistics.

There's a consultation this morning. For privacy reasons, no name or address. The caller was a woman in her 30s, who said her mother had been crying at home for four or five days, unable to see her because of isolation. Asked why, he said he could not bear it, did not know when the epidemic had passed and when life would resume, and was too old to receive effective information from the outside world, so he was very nervous and worried that he would die, even if he died, no one would know, couldn't sleep all night, walked around the room, cried all the time, didn't eat. Daughter is very anxious, there is no good way, because there is a child at home, take care of the mother, can not take care of the child, take care of the child can not take care of the mother, say again, they really want to collapse.

After consulting with Director Liu, the following intervention was given:

1. Listen. Find Resources in listening.

2. Talk. Let her talk more, and ease her anxiety in the process.

3. Evaluate. Assess the situation based on her language, speech speed, and basic information

4. Empathy. It is normal for her to feel anxious and nervous when she is in this condition.

5. accept. Accept this physical and physical response on your own.

6. Support. In the process of listening to the narrative, find the support system, stimulate their potential ability to solve the problem.

7. Advice. Take control of your emotions, ease your anxiety, and don't bring your emotions to your mom. Teach her butterfly and belly breathing.

8. Find external sources. Call Your Mother's local neighborhood committee, let them help look at the situation of your mother, and give feedback, call your mother regularly every day, and tell the outside news, encourage their confidence in overcoming difficulties.

9. Let me know how to contact director Liu Zhihong and feel free to contact us.

In the afternoon, the leaders discuss the preparation before entering the warehouse.

People are building quarantines, semi-polluted areas where we change from the shelter hospital, clean areas, and these are all the tents that have been built.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
While we were celebrating the fruits of our Labor, a strong wind blew through our tents like this.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The angels in white really need to be trained for outdoor survival. Here not only to protect others, how to protect themselves are a practical problem.

There's some good news

Saturday, February 15, rain turns to snow in Wuhan

Woke up in the early morning, looked at the time, 4:20, couldn't sleep, got up and ran around the room.

Sort through yesterday's information, found that many people sent me messages, are eye-catching Topics: yesterday Hubei Health Care Workers infected 1502 people, Wuhan Health Care Workers Infected 1102 people, killed 6..

Psychological heavy, this message sent out, the medical staff's pressure is greater. The psychological intervention will, as I predicted, be explosive.

We were ordered to put some men in the shelter, and we argued about who was going in, and everyone who came here was not a coward, but a good man. To save time, everyone in the shelter gets a bag of rations.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
We will enter the cabin, director Liu Zhihong and I talk with you about some experience, some feelings before entering the cabin, and from the cabin out of some medical staff experience, to ease the tension of everyone.

Outside the snow more and more heavy, the weather more and more cold, director Liu and I can only keep running, shaking to get their own heat.

Near noon came the good news that Conning's supplies (electric blankets, electric heaters, hot water bottles and essential supplies) had arrived, but because of the epidemic, we had to pick them up ourselves. The Post Office is 11 kilometers away, and we can't do it without a car. The chief of the local police station and the hotel manager negotiated and got it for us, which solved our problem.

Director Liu went with the car to get supplies, I was waiting. The mailman brought it to us in the snow. Thank you.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
See the General Hospital and home sent things, and Liu sent things from home, we can not wait to open, all used, we feel warm, tonight is a warm night.
